div.div: A man working a job far removed from his childhood dreams gets wrapped up in an unexpected situation…! Becoming a monster, he aims once again to fulfill his lifelong dream…! (Source: MANGA Plus) Note: - Nominated for the 14th Manga Taisho Award in 2021. - Winner of the 7th Next Manga Award in the Web Manga Category in 2021.
A special, multi-part side story manga set in the world of Mairimashita! Iruma-kun, focusing on Kalego during his days as a student of Babyls Demon School.

The modern world is one of diversity, where "genjins" live together with humans. At Keiki High School, where many genjins attend, a human boy, Yutaka Shinsou, enrolls there. Yutaka, who often goes along with other people's wishes instead of expressing his own feelings, meets a werewolf girl, Tsumiki Ogami. With Tsumiki, he has a feeling that he'll finally be able to be himself...... A new-normal story about two people's coming-of-age!

(Source: Sunday Webry, translated) Note: - Ranked 3rd place in the Tsugimanga 2024 Award in the Print Manga Category.
Boku no Kokoro no Yabai Yatsu

Ichikawa Kyoutarou, a boy barely clinging to the bottom rung of his school’s social ladder, secretly believes he’s the tortured lead in some psychological thriller. He spends his days dreaming up ways to disrupt his classmates’ peaceful lives and pining after Anna Yamada, the class idol. But Kyotaro’s not nearly the troubled teen he pretends to be…and it turns out Anna’s a bit odd herself! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Notes: - Winner of the Tsugi ni Kuru Web Manga 2020 Award. - Nominee for the 2020 Manga Taisho Award.
